==History==
The first permanent Constitution of Sudan was drafted in 1973.{{cn|date=June 2014}} It incorporated the [[Addis Ababa Agreement (1972)]] ending the first Sudanese civil war.{{cn|date=June 2014}}
On 1 July 1998, a new constitution entered into force<ref>{{cite web
| url        = http://www.icrc.org/ihl-nat.nsf/0/d728f18be88d9482c1256dc600507f33/$FILE/Constitution%20Sudan%20-%20EN.pdf
| title      = Constitution Of The Republic Of Sudan (Entered into force 1 July 1998)
| publisher  = [[International Committee of the Red Cross]]
| accessdate = 2014-06-01
}}</ref>
after being approved in the [[Sudanese constitutional referendum, 1998|constitutional referendum]].<ref name=Nohlen>Nohlen, D, Krennerich, M & Thibaut, B (1999) ''Elections in Africa: A data handbook'', p595 {{ISBN|0-19-829645-2}}</ref>
The current ''Interim National Constitution of the Republic of Sudan, 2005'' (INC) was adopted on 6 July 2005.<ref name=inc2005/>

