[[File:Père-Lachaise - Division 9 - Breton 01.jpg|thumb|[[Père Lachaise Cemetery]].]]

'''François Pierre Hippolyte Ernest Breton''', a French artist and [[Archaeology|archaeologist]], was born in Paris in 1812. He studied under Regnier, Watelet, and
[[Jean-Jacques Champin|Champin]], and exhibited some landscapes at the [[Salon (Paris)|Salon]]. He contributed to [[Jules Gailhabaud|Gailhabaud]]'s 'Monuments anciens et modernes,' and in 1843 published 'Monuments de tous les Peuples.' His latest works were 'Pompeia,' 1855 ; 'Athènes,' 1861 ; and 'L'Alhambra,' 1873. He died in Paris in 1875.

