{{Infobox book | name = While Mortals Sleep | title_orig = <!--n/a--> | translator = <!--n/a--> | image = WhileMortalsSleep.jpg | caption = First edition | author = [[Kurt Vonnegut]] | illustrator = <!--n/a--> | cover_artist = [[Kurt Vonnegut]] | country = United States | language = English | series = <!--n/a--> | subject = <!--n/a--> | genre = | publisher = [[Delacorte Press]] | release_date = [[2011 in literature|2011]] | media_type = | pages = 272 | isbn = 978-0-385-34373-2 | preceded_by = [[Look at the Birdie]] | followed_by = }}
'''''While Mortals Sleep''''' is a collection of sixteen previously unpublished short stories by [[Kurt Vonnegut]], released on January 25, 2011. It is the third posthumously published Kurt Vonnegut book, the first being ''[[Armageddon in Retrospect]]'', the second being ''[[Look at the Birdie]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sheehan|first1=William|title=Book review: 'While Mortals Sleep' by Kurt Vonnegut|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/14/AR2011021406069.html|accessdate=18 February 2017|agency=Washington Post|date=February 15, 2011}}</ref> The book begins with a foreword by [[Dave Eggers]]. Illustrations by Vonnegut himself appear throughout.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hopley|first1=Claire|title=BOOK REVIEW: ‘While Mortals Sleep’|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2011/apr/1/book-review-while-mortals-sleep/|accessdate=18 February 2017|publisher=The Washington Times|date=April 1, 2011}}</ref>
